OL,6,F"The defendant had expressed, during
OL,7,Fthe time of his arrest and whilst in
OL,8,Fcustody, that his actions were
OL,9,Finspired by the Israel-Hamas conflict.
OL,10,FHe appeared to have developed a
OL,11,Ffixation with the events there.
OL,13,F"International conflicts can create a
OL,14,Fmix of outrage, grief and grievance
OL,15,Fwhich has the potential to galvanise
OL,16,Fthose with an extremist or potentially
OL,17,Fextremist mind-set to take action.
OL,18,FSadly, as we have seen in this case,
OL,19,Fit can have devastating consequences.
